The paper discusses the development of an agent-based simulation model to understand the relationship between human resource management practices and retail productivity. This involves expertise from work psychologists and computer scientists, indicating a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The simulation model also includes features related to the spread of word of mouth, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for intelligent agents to foster sustainable organizational capabilities, which could relate to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
